  "prompt": "Who is the old man in the MDH Masala ads and why does he appear in all their ads?",
  "response": "The old man featured in the MDH Masala ads is Mahashay Dharampal Gulati, who was the owner and face of MDH (Mahashian Di Hatti) Spices. He became widely recognized due to his appearances in the advertisements for the company's products. Gulati, often referred to as the 'MDH Uncle,' was not only the owner but also a key figure in building the brand's image. His presence in the ads was meant to convey a sense of authenticity and trust, reinforcing the idea of a family-run business with deep-rooted values in quality and tradition. Dharampal Gulati was celebrated for his longevity and work ethic, and he became an iconic figure in Indian advertising.",
